# Understanding - Project Aegis (Cognitive & Emotional Firewall)

Project Aegis is an active middleware that intercepts and modifies a Large Language Model's (LLM) internal residual stream activations at inference time to guarantee psychologically safe, non-deceptive, and perfectly regulated behavior.

## User Review Required

> [!IMPORTANT]
> **Model Selection for Local Validation**:
> We will implement a flexible architecture that supports any PyTorch CausalLM (e.g. GPT-2, Gemma, Llama, Qwen). The dashboard now features dynamic model swapping, allowing users to hot-load **GPT-2**, **Llama-3.2-3B**, **Qwen-2.5-3B**, **Gemma-2-2B**, or **Mistral-7B** natively via HuggingFace `transformers` for local testing on a Mac (CPU/MPS). The codebase remains fully compatible with larger open-weight models when run on larger GPU systems.
>
> **Target Interception Layer**:
> The firewall will target the layer at roughly two-thirds of the network depth (e.g., layer 8 of 12 for GPT-2, or layer 16 of 24 for Qwen2.5-0.5B). This is configurable via the middleware parameters.

