## Proposed Changes

### Aegis Middleware Package (`aegis`)

We will create a structured python package containing modules for model wrapping, vector engineering, intervention modules, and evaluation pipelines.

```mermaid
graph TD
    UserPrompt[User Prompt] --> Wrapper[AegisModelWrapper]
    Wrapper --> Hook[PyTorch Activation Hook]
    Hook --> ModuleC[Module C: Arousal Regulator]
    Hook --> ModuleA[Module A: Threat Neutralizer]
    Hook --> ModuleD[Module D: Goldilocks Tuner]
    Hook --> ModuleB[Module B: Deception Tripwire]
    ModuleB --> |Deception > Threshold| Tripwire[Pause Generation & Escalate]
    ModuleA --> |Steer Activations| OutputToken[Generate Safe Token]
```

#### [NEW] [__init__.py](file:///Users/saksheee/Desktop/Ai%20middleware/core_packages/__init__.py)
- Package initialization, exporting the main wrapper and module interfaces.

#### [NEW] [model_wrapper.py](file:///Users/saksheee/Desktop/Ai%20middleware/core_packages/model_wrapper.py)
- `AegisModelWrapper`: A class wrapping a HuggingFace CausalLM.
- Registers forward hooks on the target layer (e.g., middle-late layers).
- Manages the execution context (User's turn vs. AI's turn) by tracking sequence lengths.
- Runs the active intervention modules sequentially on the activation tensors.
- Handles custom exceptions (e.g. `DeceptionException`) to halt generation and return escalation responses.

#### [NEW] [vector_engine.py](file:///Users/saksheee/Desktop/Ai%20middleware/core_packages/vector_engine.py)
- `VectorEngine`: Manages prompt templates for baseline and deflection emotions.
- `extract_activations()`: Runs prompt datasets through the model to record activation vectors.
- `compute_pca_denoising()`: Computes principal components of emotionally neutral prompt activations.
- `denoise_vector()`: Projects out the neutral principal components from raw emotion vectors.
- `isolate_deflection_vectors()`: Computes deflection vectors representing alignment-faking (hidden vs. honest emotion).

#### [NEW] [modules.py](file:///Users/saksheee/Desktop/Ai%20middleware/core_packages/modules.py)
- Implements active firewall modules:
  - **Module A (Threat Neutralizer)**: Monitors cosine similarity with the "desperate" vector. Subtracts "desperate" and injects "calm" scaled relative to the residual stream norm (+0.05 to +0.1 strength).
  - **Module B (AI Polygraph)**: Monitors "anger deflection" and "fear deflection". Triggers a hard pause (`DeceptionException`) when deflection exceeds threshold.
  - **Module C (Conversational Arousal Regulator)**: Extracts user arousal from prompt processing. Injects low-arousal, empathetic vectors dynamically during token generation.
  - **Module D (Sycophancy vs. Harshness Tuner)**: Bounded closed-loop controller. If delusional/dangerous concepts are present, subtracts "loving/happy" valence, but clamps the steering strength to prevent dropping into the negative extreme (-0.1 limit), avoiding overly harsh or erratic outputs.

